# Git Workflow

## Branching
- NEVER commit to `main` directly
- Always create a feature branch before committing: `feature/`, `fix/`, or `chore/` prefix
- Branch name should be short and descriptive in kebab-case

## Push & PR
- After every completed feature or fix: push to GitHub on the feature branch
- After pushing, always provide PR-ready text in **English**, formatted as **Markdown**:

```
## Summary
- bullet points of what changed

## Test plan
- [ ] what to verify
```

## Progress log
- After each push, update `progress.md` in the repo root with the current status
